  "response": "Here's a detailed breakdown:\n\nB-Schools accepting GMAT:\n1. IIM Bangalore\n2. IIM Ahmedabad\n3. IIM Calcutta\n4. XLRI Jamshedpur\n5. Indian School of Business (ISB), Hyderabad\n6. SPJIMR Mumbai\n7. Great Lakes Chennai\n8. MDI Gurgaon\n\nCAT vs GMAT for IIMs:\n\u2022 CAT is still the primary entrance exam for most IIMs\n\u2022 GMAT is accepted as an alternative at select IIMs\n\u2022 CAT is generally considered easier to prepare for Indian students\n\u2022 GMAT has a more standardized global format\n\u2022 GMAT scores are valid for 5 years, while CAT is annual\n\nRecommendation:\n\u2022 If targeting traditional IIM admission: Prepare for CAT\n\u2022 If looking for flexibility: Consider GMAT\n\u2022 Check specific IIM requirements for each campus\n\u2022 Some IIMs have specific GMAT score cut-offs\n\nAdditional Tips:\n\u2022 GMAT scores can be useful for international MBA applications\n\u2022 Prepare thoroughly regardless of exam choice\n\u2022 Academic profile and work experience also matter significantly\n\nConsult individual institute websites for most updated admission criteria.",
